Adjective:

1. A necessary component of something; a necessary component that, with other parts or factors, constitues a whole.

Noun: 

2. ''Mathematics''  Also called '''Antiderivative or Riemann Integral''' a). A numerical measure computed by a limiting process in which the domain of a function is divided into small subintervals and the value of the function at a point in each subinterval is multiplied by the measurement of that subinterval, and all products thereto are summed. Its symbol appears similar to an elongated "S".